Hector Bellerin on London: &quot;My family settled there with me, although now, for family reasons, they have had to return to Barcelona.&quot;<br />
<br />
Bellerin: &quot;I have a tougher time now because I'm a family person, I depend on them a lot, and it'll be a new challenge to be without them.&quot;

Mario Lemina: &quot;Arsenal? I&rsquo;m at a very big club but haven&rsquo;t been able to show my qualities so it&rsquo;s flattering that big clubs are showing up.&quot;<br />
<br />
Mario Lemina: &quot;If I leave I&rsquo;d like an experience with a club abroad. [Lyon or Marseille?] I don&rsquo;t think that would be the right move.&quot;
